    <criterion testable="true">notes/lessons-learned.md exists with required phase-specific insights (PR #363, INV-5, NFR-10/11, A.5, halt-loud).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">notes/handoffs/ contents archived under notes/.archive/.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Final task. Cannot start until all of (053, 060, 061, 073, 074) are ✅. Critical issues found by code-review or adr-check require remediation tasks (file them, fix them, re-run the gate) BEFORE this task completes.

    Lessons-learned is not a checkbox — write it as a real artifact future projects will read. Be honest about what went badly, not just what went well. The high-risk items in TASK-INDEX.md (PR #363 sequencing, stale dist/, halt-loud) are the prompts for this — what actually happened?

    After this task is ✅, the project is closed. The next reasonable action is `/merge-to-master` or PR creation if not already done.
  </notes>

